[SN]TITLE[SN]
West Belfast rally held after attacks on pensioners

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Several hundred people have attended a rally in west Belfast after a number of recent violent robberies in which elderly residents were targeted.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
4 February 2016 Last updated at 14:54 GMT
It was held close to the scene of one of the attacks, in which a 76-year-old woman suffered a broken jaw.
Personal alarms and safety packs are to be distributed to older people in the area, as Catherine Morrison reports.
